{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "{PROJECT_NAME} AI Instructions Auto-Sync",
  "description": "Automatically syncs AI instruction files across all platforms when modified",
  "version": "1.0",
  "when": {
    "type": "fileEdited",
    "patterns": [
      "AGENTS.md",
      "CLAUDE.md",
      "GEMINI.md",
      ".github/copilot-instructions.md",
      ".vscode/README.md",
      ".zed/README.md",
      "ai-agents/*.md"
    ],
    "branches": ["main", "develop", "feature/*", "hotfix/*"]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "tool": "tools/ai-instructions-sync.ps1",
    "arguments": ["-Action", "sync-all"],
    "prompt": "ðŸ”„ AI INSTRUCTION FILE MODIFIED - SYNC REQUIRED\n\nAn AI instruction file has been changed. Execute the synchronization process:\n\n1. Run sync tool: `./tools/ai-instructions-sync.ps1 -Action sync-all`\n2. Validate sync: `./tools/ai-instructions-sync.ps1 -Action validate`\n3. Verify all platforms synchronized:\n   - `AGENTS.md` (MASTER SOURCE)\n   - `.github/copilot-instructions.md` (GitHub Copilot)\n   - `CLAUDE.md` (Claude AI)\n   - `GEMINI.md` (Google Gemini AI)\n   - `.vscode/README.md` (VS Code)\n   - `.zed/README.md` (Zed Editor)\n   - `ai-agents/*.md` (All agents)\n\nSuccess criteria:\nâœ… All platforms synchronized\nâœ… No sync conflicts\nâœ… Multi-OS paths correct\nâœ… Agent files updated\n\nConfirm completion and report any issues."
  }
}
